      {"@type":"Question","name":"How quickly can you collect e-waste from my office?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Same-day to 48-hour turnaround is standard. We offer 4-hour emergency service for urgent corporate needs. Priority same-day slots are available for Infopark, Smart City, and Kakkanad."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What is ITAD and do I need it for my business?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"ITAD stands for IT Asset Disposition - the certified, auditable process of retiring IT equipment. Any business handling personal or financial data is legally required to use certified ITAD to comply with DPDP Act 2023 and India's E-Waste Rules 2022."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"Where can I recycle e-waste near me in Kochi?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our main facility is at 710A Hill Palace Road, Thrippunithura, Kochi - open Mon-Sat 8AM-8PM, Sun 10AM-4PM. We also offer free pickup across all Ernakulam zones: Infopark, Kakkanad, Smart City, Edappally, MG Road, Vytilla, Aluva and more."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What electronics do you accept for recycling?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We accept all 21 categories under India's E-Waste Rules 2022: laptops, desktops, servers, phones, tablets, TVs, monitors, printers, networking gear, batteries, UPS, air conditioners, refrigerators, washing machines and more."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"How do you destroy data from hard drives and SSDs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We use NIST SP 800-88 and DoD 5220.22-M certified methods: cryptographic erase for SSDs, degaussing for HDDs, and physical shredding for ultimate security. Every device receives a unique Certificate of Destruction with serial number documentation."}}
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
